Awesome local coffee house. Best homemade soups! And pastries. Can't wait to go back. I'm not into soup, but they offered such wonderfully unusual cconcoctions that I had to try one. It had cactus in its description. It did NOT disappoint! Nice little place, friendly atmosphere. All ages had come in and out in the short time I was enjoying an espresso masterpiece. They have board games and an outdoor eating area. It's small and has limited parking but they've made great use of the small space. Its worth it. Inventive paint and design scheme, good music - but nothing over the top, screaming "We're woke" or "Coffee Snobs without Jobs," or "Your seventh shot of espresso is free.*" *Redeemable only ONCE per day, people. WHY are you STILL at work? Don't you sleep? ever? Go home already - your coffee jitters are giving  coffee jitters to my coffee jitters." Truth be told, I've never come across the cafe with, "It's called espresso, NOT ex-presso," snobbery except once at a DC Starpunks, and in that case, I actually think it was just a one-time bad day for the barista. So. Either way, good stuff. Keep it up, Aroma Cafe. Looking forward to returning.
